- The Kinect now has three &quot;cameras&quot;, one of which is actually the emitter of infrared rays and the second the receiver of the reflected signal.
But the third camera is really just a visible fingerboard sensor.
This is not used to determine the depth of the object.
Potentially more cameras could solve the problem...
Or on the contrary, increase it and increase the required number of calculations.
It would be nice to create a flexible analogue of the Kinect, play around with the curvature of camera placement and see how this would help determine the three-dimensional position.
- As far as I remember, Microsoft, unlike Google, has not presented its glasses to the public.
