Infectologist and HIV/AIDS expert, Andrade Villanueva commented that since 2008, scientists had concluded that AIDS was not a fatal sentence, but the years of survival and quality of life depend on the degree of affectation to the immune system that they present patients at the beginning of the diagnosis, with a better expectation for those who are not drug users: up to 30 years with a CD4 count of 200 and 50 years, when they report 500 CD4.
